ğŸŒ HOW BANDWIDTH WORKS IN PRACTICE

At runtime, the girl has a current state (energy, mood, attitude, etc.). Before each action, she (or the system) checks:

```
if current_energy < bandwidth.energy_range[0] or current_energy > bandwidth.energy_range[1]:
    trigger("low_energy_crisis")   # she feels drained, might withdraw
if current_mood not in bandwidth.mood_allowed:
    trigger("mood_spill")           # she's acting out of character
if abs(current_attitude) > bandwidth.attitude_range[1] or abs(current_attitude) < bandwidth.attitude_range[0]:
    trigger("attitude_flip")        # she's too resistant or too cooperative
```

The expression_stretch determines how quickly she returns to baseline after a deviation. A high stretch means she's flexible; a low stretch means she's brittle and may break character entirely.

The Brat Emissary (a background process) holds the full seed and periodically compares the girl's recent history against it. If she's drifting too far, the Emissary can inject a "grounding" eventâ€”a memory, a whisper, a sudden feeling of "this isn't me."

